@node "Help" "Help me"

If you find a new device, please EMail me at 

                             age@thepentagon.com

or/and tell me the latest versions.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
       devices               Size               Version  (Date)
         Copyright:
         Used by:
         Available:
         Your correct E-Mail or/and WWW-address:

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

If you dont know the infos about the devices, so send me please an E-Mail
with the -> uucoded Lha-File <- of this devices.
So I can include the information with your name in the next release of this
guide.

         - Great thanks -

@Endnode

@node "What" "What I used?"
Roger HÍgensen      - "DVC" V2.2 - check the version and update any kind 
                      of file
                    - Aminet - util/sys/DVC.lha

Jan Schwenke        - "EasyFind" V1.11 - Aminet - util/dir/EasyFind.lha
                    - an easy to use program to look for files (DTypes)
                      on any device 

Amiga Technologies  - "C:Version xxx.library file full"

Heiko Schr—der      - "DTypeLha" (an ARexx-script to extract .datatype-files
                                of an .lha-file, full automatized)
                    - not released

Heiko Schr—der      - "VerAmos" (an Amos-program to looking for the version,
                                 date and author)
                    - not released and no more needed (look at DVC ;-)

Heiko Schr—der      - "SearchIn£Device.guide¨" to release the "New.guide"
                      and the "Update.guide"
                    - released with this Guide

@Endnode


